Test 1:

In about:addons go to Options ⚙️ and select "Debug Add-ons."
about:debugging#/runtime/this-firefox is loaded in a new tab.

Test 2:

In about:addons go to Options ⚙️ and select "manage Extensions Shortcuts"
"manage extension Shortcuts" section is loaded and
each extension casseste contain the extension name and shortcuts.
Extension that do not have shortcuts are listed at the the bottom of the page under the line"The following extensions do not have shortcuts:"

Select one of the shortcut fields.
Field is highlighted while selected.

Type in a shortcut in one of the shortcut fields using CTRL /ALT as the first key.
A tooltip will appear with the suggestion to type another letter.

Add a shortcut which is not used,
Key combination is saved. When focus is set on the field it will show as empty aside the "Type a shortcut suggestion"

Delete Shortcut.
Shortcut is deleted and the field will show as empty even when not in focus.

Click on the Back button on the left side of the "Manage Extension Shortcuts" header.
User is returned to last visited section.

